    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just \"random coincidences\" though. i can feel it. like a physical sensation in my chest when the \"echo\" is near. and it isn't just one thing, it's happening more often now. if it was just stress, i'd be able to explain why that specific mug meant a car crash was going to happen. but i can't. it's like the object is just... holding the energy of what's about to occur. don't you think there could be a scientific reason for it? like some kind of temporal residue or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
