    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just feel like you're being too dismissive with the \"mainstream science\" thing. i know what i felt. it felt realer than the actual event sometimes. if science hasn't caught up to how people actually experience reality yet, does that mean it's not happening? what if there's a way to actually measure this kind of residue? like, how would one even begin to look for evidence of something that exists outside of linear time?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
